  "title": "Electrical Engineer (Entry Level)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a <strong>Marine and Offshore Industry.</strong> Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a Electrical Engineer to be part of their Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the <strong>West </strong>- easily accessible.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and develop control systems.</li><li>Prepare drawings for customer review and approval.</li><li>Create drawings and BCM documentation for shop floor production.</li><li>Coordinate with clients, consultants, and internal teams to ensure project alignment.</li><li>Perform drafting and design work using CAD software (AutoCAD/SolidWorks).</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Min Diploma in Electrical Engineering or equivalent discipline</li><li>Familiar in<strong> AutoCAD</strong></li><li>Entry-level candidates are welcome to apply. On-the-job training will be provided.</li></ul><p><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em><br /><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em><br /><br /><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em><br /></a><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em><br /><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em><br /><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
